##Random Talk, Ie the appearance of sentient beings under a mask

Micro-signal Mengbeiyu

Feature Introduction, an anachronistic cynic's thought and attempt.

On Harvard: Life under the mask

The first story: Red Things easy to change, white things hard to persuade

Gui Youguang from the administrative office sent me a message, which was forwarded to me by the county government. The source came from the mailbox of the mayor of Sanjiang City: People in the Meihuagou community reported that the cadres in the Meihuagou community had not acted properly, and an elderly family in the community had died, during the outbreak, there was a feast.

I immediately got in touch with Jin Chunhe, the secretary of the Meihuagou community. Jin Chunhe was a young man, two years older than me. He used to be the secretary of the Meihuagou community. Later, after the secretary of the Meihuagou community resigned due to health problems, became the new secretary of Meihuagou.

The other end of the line, Jin Chunhe, was still listening, and he said, well, I know we've been there twice, and it's kind of small now. The deceased was an old man with three sons and two daughters, a large family. Although the sons and daughters were not very rich and expensive, they were still doing well and could afford a car of 100,000 yuan. At first they were going to set up 40 tables, but in the morning we tried to persuade him to freeze all the food he had bought. Before lunch we tried again. At least there were only six tables set up for lunch. To tell the truth, our community cadres do not have the power to enforce the law. People have already given them a lot of face. When they tried to persuade them the second time, the atmosphere was already very tense. They almost quarreled with the people who were having dinner. If we go again, there will probably be a conflict. I think if we really want him to stop, we have to take coercive measures and let the police from the police station handle it. Didn't the county government issue documents? As for the host and the Cook of the family feast during the epidemic period, they all had to be dealt with according to the law. I heard that many of the dead people in the family in Niaoyuhuazhen are now having funerals. This morning my upstairs neighbor went to the relatives'funeral in Shanjie village because the government was shouting loudly, but in fact no one has been dealt with yet. Or we can start with our community, arrest this family and the Cook, and detain them for a few days, as a demonstration effect, which will surely scare off the people of Niaoyuhuazhen and even the people of Ziwu County who are holding funerals, and turn the tide."

"It's not that simple, " I said. "The police stations are also cautious and don't arrest people so easily. In these troubled times, the Chinese value the dead above all else. They arrest people at sensitive times like funerals. The police stations are also afraid of mass incidents. We're afraid of Keyboardist, but the police at the police station are even more afraid. If they can send the body to the county funeral home to be frozen for a while, then they can hold the funeral after the epidemic has passed! In addition, you go to investigate who they invited the Taoist priest, consult with the Taoist priest, even buy some gifts and bribes, say that the recent 'bad luck' and so on, it's bad for the children and grandchildren, people are most afraid of what's wrong with the children and grandchildren, and then suggest that the funeral be held at another time. That's it. If we have to do it again tonight, we'll call the police and do it the hard way."

Jin Chunhe exclaimed: "This kind of thing has no way, how can persuade AH, unless hard, compulsory implementation, our community cadres stand around to persuade half a day, people simply ignore you. ". With so many forms to report, our community cadres still stood there and talked for half a day. The funeral could not be persuaded. It was not like getting married, moving house or celebrating one's birthday! According to the custom in the countryside, no ten or eight people can not be carried up the mountain to be buried."

The second story: Form Grasp Epidemic Prevention, data show achievements

Long term repression must lead to a general outbreak. These two days I have experienced first hand the pressure of the epidemic front, but unfortunately it is more from the formalism, the first step for a new civil servant to change into a veteran is: he suddenly doesn't know what he is working for, he doesn't know what the meaning of what he does every day, slowly he comes to understand a truth, since there is no meaning, so why try?

Starting at 09:21 this morning and ending at 18:24 this afternoon, the administration office, Gui Youguang, sent me a total of 22 superior documents, all of which are fresh today, still steaming! I spent the whole day walking, climbing stairs, knocking on doors, and working until 22:00 pm. As president, I worked until 1:30 am. It was 2:40 when I got home to wash and go to bed, of course, there's always someone who works harder than you. The deputy mayor of Xiansun told me today that he got off work at 4:00 a.m. last night, and that knocking on the door of a farmer's house at 1:00 a.m. and asking him to answer questions and fill out forms is not a good working experience. And even with all this overtime, it's still way past the deadline set by county Party Secretary Gamow -- 18:00 p.m, so today, together with other towns, we received a red-headed notice from the county's coronavirus prevention and Control Committee.

Su Ru just called me to see her, asked me why our town was notified? I said, a lot of townships have been notified. The ones that have not been notified are all small townships with very small populations, and basically the larger and more populous townships have been notified. I'm not talking about that, I'm talking about this! Su Ru took out a red-headed document placed in front of me.

I looked, is a statistical identity of the township staff information, physical condition, Spring Festival travel, family relations table, but I did not see this table yesterday. I mean, this form just came in today, right?

Su Ru said, you look at the date, it is issued yesterday. I looked at the date, and it turned out that the date was written yesterday. I thought maybe there were too many documents missing. After all, there are so many documents every day. We usually first determine whether the document needs to be replied to, and if it does, we Click on it and try to respond; if we don't need to, we don't click on it at all. At this time I would feel sorry for the people at the county level. They have racked their brains to hand out the hard-written documents. If there is nothing constructive in them, no one will notice if you put a dirty word in them, because most people don't watch it. If it's not a standard document, we usually skip the text and go straight to the attached form, because the attached form is the real thing, and most people at the grass roots don't have the time to appreciate the style of the draftsman.

In the middle of this paragraph, Gui Youguang sent two documents, warmly celebrate today to receive the "county-level epidemic prevention documents" the number of 24! Let's see, it's 19:01 p.m. , and I got my first file from 9:21 a.m. , which means I got a file every 26 minutes, on average, during that time, 26 minutes, that's basically just enough time to read the documents, but our job isn't just to read them, we have to not only read them, we have to implement them, and a lot of them have to be filed.

At 17:48 p.m. , poppy (the young first-time civil servant who was willing to try out with me) handed me a document that said, "here, look at it, starting tomorrow! " I read the document, issued by the Health Bureau, i have to say that the document issued by the Health Bureau has at least one advantage. That is, it is concise. A red-headed document contains only one paragraph, starting tomorrow, every two days, a news bulletin will be sent to the Department of Health about the work of the COVID-19, with pictures.

I said angrily to the poppy, "It seems that they don't think we are busy enough! I wonder, doesn't the propaganda department want us to send them Daily News Bulletins? Why is the Health Department doing this again? Why can't they just share information?"

Papaver Rhoeas patted me on the back, "Oh, don't be angry, " he said. "I told them, AH, the health bureau said, this is different. The News Bulletin sent to the Health Bureau can not be the same as the news bulletin sent to the propaganda department. The focus is different. " I could not refute it, if they say it's not the same, then it's not the same.

If it doesn't break in silence, it will break in silence, Lu Xun said. Wait... that's really what Lu Xun said!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
So this afternoon, there was an outcry in the crowd. Ah Heng of Chengguan, Chamdo complained in the "epidemic prevention and control" group, then the deputy township head of Mingyue Township echoed, the deputy township head of Mingyue Township's underlings complained, the mayor of Chengguan, Chamdo also began to complain, with these big bosses take the lead, everyone doubled in courage, dare to publicly accuse the "county coronavirus prevention and Control Committee" deployment of confusion. Here's a screenshot of some of the comments posted: (some of the leaks and dialects are pixelated)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Although the "censure" seems generally mild, I think it is entirely because we are towns, they are county organs, or I guess all kinds of curse words are unavoidable to blurt out. After all, time is money, time is life, wasting other people's time is tantamount to murder for money. Lu Xun is said to have said the same thing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As I typed the above, today's 25th document arrived, but this time not from Gui Youguang, but from Duan Qin. To put it simply, the political and Legal Committee of Ziwu County requested that the towns and townships compile dozens of statistics by 12 noon tomorrow. Everyone wants to show his face at this critical time. How can I be absent from the political and Legal Committee of Daziwu County? Let's take a look at the contents of the file: (condensed version)

Your township organizations mobilize cadres, police, grid, patrol members, grass-roots d members, as well as various social organizations, enterprises, the masses, volunteers and other forces x people. As of October X, a total of x 10,000 households and x 10,000 people, accounting for x% of the total number of households, were visited. Check risk hidden trouble x, resolve all kinds of contradictions and disputes according to law XX pieces. Send out police X person-times, strengthen the control of social order, set up XX police stations, x patrol vehicles in accordance with the established grid to carry out patrol work. X number of police personnel deployed, x fixed checkpoints, x temporary checkpoints, x strictly inspect passing vehicles and personnel, a total of x sets of disinfection vehicles; X sets of inspection vehicles from other places, x sets of returnees, x sets of Aliens; X sets of local vehicles, migrants X persons. Using XX platform channel, collect XXX and other information related to the reported epidemic a total of XXX. By using new media such as Wechat, Weibo, Qq, Douyin, etc. , we have cumulatively issued XX articles on legal knowledge, videos and information related to the epidemic situation, monitored and found XX articles on negative public sentiment related to the epidemic situation, and investigated and dealt with XX names of persons who issued false information about the epidemic situation on the Internet in accordance with the law.

Requirements: reporting features, working practices, measures, the number of words is not limited. Data to be accurate, such as the basic realization of XX, probably XX, XX more than the number of people and other mold and phrases

This is the urgent document issued by the county political and legal committee at 20:00 today, which requires all departments, such as townships and police stations, to submit by 12:00 tomorrow morning. To be honest, as for myself, I really don't see it, how urgent this is.

Data, files and forms are the fig leaf of a few bureaucrats, and also their "golden oil" , poverty alleviation, environmental protection, economy, epidemic prevention... ... forms can be used to do almost anything to cover up their lack of ability to do practical work. We satirize this called "form epidemic prevention, data achievements. ".

The third story: The petitioners

Ziwu County is where the first case of coronavirus infection was confirmed in Sanjiang, meaning that in the first two days only Ziwu County was confirmed among the city's one million people. The municipal government attaches great importance, the mayor will personally come to Ziwu county to see how things are handled, in this "talk about the color change of coronavirus" period, everyone's attention on this matter is very high.

Two days ago, Wu Chunqiu called me, let me immediately back to the Office for a meeting, I thought that there is a new case of coronavirus. When we got to the office, everyone had already arrived, except for yue-wen ou, wu Chunqiu said: "Now the situation is like this, the mayor will come to Ziwu County soon to inspect the treatment of cases of coronavirus pneumonia, as well as our county's preparation work, will come soon. ". But the news was somehow known to the two visiting families, and now they may have to go to the car stop, or just make a scene. If so, it will be troublesome, now we are divided into two groups, director Kou of the Judicial Institute and I will go to the community cadres immediately, together to stabilize the first family; Duan Qin and Sima Kun will go together, later on Owen came to his car, to the village first to find the branch secretary, watch the second family, keep quiet, you talk about work in the vicinity, to see if she went out, if she went out, just follow her, to see if she went to the isolation point. Meng Beiyu, keep watch in the office. If there is anything you need, I will call you right away. You can help me run errands or prepare materials."

These meetings are always very short. After a few minutes, they left. I waited in my office. Deputy Mayor Li Niangang, who is in charge of security, came in, "just as it happens, " he said, "you will draw up a notice for me on the resumption of work in the factories in the town during the epidemic period to strengthen the work of safety and epidemic prevention. This is to sterilize, take the temperature of the employees every day, and the employees will wear masks. If anything happens, first quarantine it and report it to the government immediately. I will change it after you write it down. "

When I finished writing the draft and Vice Mayor Li finished revising it, I took it to the administrative office and printed out the official documents. Director Wu and his family have already returned. The two petitioners are in a relatively stable mood. The mayor has also completed the on-site inspection, he's at a county meeting right now, and after that, he's headed back to downtown Tam Giang, so there's no reason to be alarmed. And they'll be back.

Fourth Story: Isolated Observation Point location conflict

The county government required that each township must set up isolated observation points, which must be easily accessible, equipped with water, electricity and other conditions, have adequate accommodation, and be 500 meters away from the population centers, which puzzled the leaders of Niaoyuhuazhen, scratched his head trying to find the right spot to observe.

But soon they found a very suitable place, that is, Yuhe village, where the original villagers committee was. Yuhe village original villagers committee in the Hillside, the building area is not small, plus the meeting room, library, villagers activity room, can be divided into about 40 rooms. Later, when Yuhe village and Ruhai village merged, the office position of Ruhai village was newly built and more lofty and grand, so the office position of Hehai village after the merger was fixed at the position of the former Ruhai village, the office of Yuhe village was used as a place for the villagers'activities.

In the past, there were more families on the mountain. Now people are getting rich. There are few people living on the mountain. Many people have moved down the mountain to live. So there are no settlements on the mountain, just a dozen families scattered all over the place. So the leaders from the scene to check back, immediately identified in the original Yuhe Village Office position based on the transformation of a temporary isolation observation point out, for the observation of suspected carriers and close contacts.

But the project had just begun in the morning, and by noon almost all the villagers in the hills were blocking the work. When they heard that they were going to set up an observation post in their village for people at high risk of suspected coronavirus pneumonia, they immediately began to talk about it, and one or two residents whose homes were closer to the village positions encouraged them to do so, immediately called family and friends to gather at the construction site and not allow the workers to start work.

As the leaders of Niaoyuhuazhen explained the safety and importance of the isolated observation point, the villagers were reluctant to let any suspected pneumonia patient into the village. After lunch, the cadres of Hehai village called to say that the former office of Yuhe village had been blocked by sand and mud brought in by several villagers, and that the workers had been driven out, the group of villagers also transported a lot of stones to block the road up the mountain. Now not only can not go up the mountain in Yuhe village, but also those driving back to the village will have to make a detour.

The epidemic did not wait for anyone, let alone allow this demonstration effect to spread. After deliberation by the leaders of Niaoyuhuazhen, the police station dispatched police forces to disperse the gathering crowd and asked the workers to clean up the blocking roads and the rubble and soil. However, after repeated consideration, work at the isolated observation point at the former Yuhe village position slowed down. As they did this ideological work to prove to the villagers that the isolated observation point would not cause the spread of disease in the village of Yuhe, Ha Hai village officials slowly carried out renovation work.

It's also because the government has found a location for another observation point. The younger brother of Pei Jiayuan, director of Quan Yan village, built a fairly large-scale farm family in the Valley of Quan Yan village. There were restaurants, private rooms, chess and card rooms, guest rooms, kitchens and so on. However, business was slow after it was completed, and farm family was canceled, the rooms are also empty, but the facilities are complete and can accommodate up to 50 quarantined personnel. The government immediately rented the old farmhouse, which was meant to be a place for people to live and relax, so it was easier to renovate than the Yuhe village office. And on the farm around the land are Director Pei Jiayuan brother contract, there is no one near the villagers, so the villagers of the spring eye village also can not oppose.

However, the government has not given up the construction of the Yuhe village position observation point either. First, in order to prevent too many people from being quarantined, the old farmers'optimistic observation point is not enough to live in. Second, as things have come to this, there is no way for them to retreat, so if they retreat in the case of an emergency outbreak, it is likely that no village in Niaoyuhuazhen can find an observation point that local villagers do not object to.

However, the villagers of the original Yuhe village did not give up. They began to use the tactic commonly used by the petitioners, namely "online rumor-mongering, " and took photos of the day when the People's police drove the villagers away and the motorcade, saying that the people's police beat people, said that day pulled more than a dozen patients to Yuhe village to the mountains to live. But in fact, the police didn't even start the operation on that day. They gave a direct warning for a while, and several villagers chickened out and slowly dispersed. Meanwhile, the observation point in Yuhe village is still under construction at present, and no one lives in it, even the entire county now has only one confirmed case and some close contacts.

Ling Sha, who had previously worked as a public opinion monitor at the county government, had experience in such matters and immediately contacted the county propaganda department and the County Public Security Bureau. Then, as is often the case, he spent several days in detention during the Spring Festival, "My name is XXX, I am from Hehai village, Niaoyuhuazhen town, Ziwu County. I posted a video on my friends' circle on the afternoon of January X. The rumor police beat people and dozens of pneumonia patients live in Hehai village. I am very sorry for my behavior... "

The fifth story: Duan Qin's narration

Last night, by order of Gan Mao, the county Party secretary, all information had to be collected by 6:00 p.m. that day. Everyone, that is to say everyone, whether you go out or not, whether you come back from the outside, even if you went down the stairs this year, you have to collect. Secretary Gan probably forgot that we are an administrative county with a population of 500,000.

So this task is absolutely impossible to accomplish, but no one can say, so when an old factory district took two days but surveyed only one third of the population, duan was one of 20 government officials sent to help the plant carry out door-to-door investigations. But Duan Qin obviously doesn't understand this job. Obviously, it's fine for people to isolate themselves at home, but the county government insists that we go door-to-door and fill out forms. If one of the staff members is infected, then thousands of people in this old factory district will probably be infected.

Duan Qin told me, they go to some people's homes, it is more normal, each other wearing a mask to complete the matter. Other oddities abound:

A certain family, Duan Qin and the community workers had just knocked on the door, Duan Qin had just revealed his identity, and the other party closed the door with a "Bang" , "I kept myself isolated at home, " he said. "You insisted on bringing the virus into my home. You cadres went from house to house. How many people do you have to contact in a day? I don't want to talk to you. " As a result of the family's investigation, the information was gathered and the forms filled out by shouting at each other through a door.

A second family, Duan Qin and the staff just knocked on the door, the other side shouted at them to go away, saying: "Go away, you are 50 meters away from me to talk to me! " Duan Qin fainted and said, you are on the fourth floor, you are not 50 meters away from the street, then why do you open the window, you are not afraid of people walking on the street to infect you AH!

And, of course, some of the residents were so enthusiastic that they invited them in for tea. Of course, Duan Qin and the others do not sit in the room. They are all just gathering information at the door.

There is a family, is back from Hubei, when Duan Qin expressed his intention. Since I returned home to Ziwu County, the traffic police have called me, the Public Security Bureau has called me, the county government has called me, the town government has called me, and the community has called me? You guys take turns calling me all the time, and I'm sick of it!"

Another thing is, when Duan Qin and the community workers came to a residential building, they actually found the Mahjong Parlour downstairs was open. There were a group of middle-aged and elderly people inside. So Duan Qin and the community workers went in to persuade them to leave. As a result, the owner of the Mahjong Club pointed to his nose and scolded him, saying, "you are harassing me, you are harassing my business, you are harassing the normal entertainment of others! " The strangest thing was that the owner of the Mahjong Club around finally called the police to arrest them, the police arrived, along with Duan Qin and the community workers, and persuaded the crowd to close the Mahjong Parlor.

There are also many residents who are so self-protective that they are unwilling to provide information. Some do not want to give their ID card numbers. Some do not even tell their names. As a result, many of the forms returned in the middle of the night are empty. Here, I would like to correct a mistake made by many people. Many people think that the government has the identity information of everyone. In fact, this is a mistake. It is the Public Security Bureau, not the government, that has the identity information of everyone, except in an emergency, the Public Security Bureau doesn't give out people's identities to government agencies.

It is true that we can learn the identity of some people when they go through the formalities, but we can not find out the identity of many people unless we can collect and accumulate it. But the staff of the county government is very "strict" , anyone who does not write ID card number, or telephone number, or itinerary, the county staff will not receive the form. If he doesn't take it, you don't pay it, and then you file a complaint the next day.

But I found out after the statistics, we feel out of 2600 out of the returnees, of which 400 did not tell staff ID number. At that time the county Party Committee Standing Committee, Bird Language Flower Township squatting leadership Wang Gang, right next to me.

I asked Wang, what to do?

Wang said, "is it all right not to have an ID card? "?

I mean, the county won't take it, and if they don't, they're gonNA report it tomorrow.

Wang said, then let the village community cadres to ask what is the identity number!

It's 11:30 at night, I said, and it could take a long time for community leaders, who have been busy all day, to knock on doors, wake up people who are already asleep, and persuade them to provide ID numbers. (what I was going to say was that I wouldn't finish until tomorrow.)

Wang, hesitating, said, that must be done according to the requirements!

Then director Du Yumen came over and asked me in a low voice, then you said how to do? I said, make it up, and I'm sure there's a lot of that in other towns, just a lot of it. Du Yumen thought for a moment and said, then make up a story and report the form earlier. The data was not accurate in the first place. The data of one hundred thousand people suddenly had to be visited all over today. It was impossible at all, it's an astronomical number, so fake it!

I said, okay, but make it up regularly, and it takes an hour or two. By the time I had filled out every blank, it was 1:00 in the morning. I finally sent the form to the staff of the county government! So wet road, I ride a small electric donkey back to the county, although it is not very far, but if the fall dead, is not an industrial injury? !

If I were to fall to my death now, or catch pneumonia and die, would I have any regrets? Yeah, I've never had a girlfriend. I'm talking about a real girlfriend, not a hand-holding, mouth-kissing kind of girlfriend.

The fifth story..

Wait, I've only told four stories, and I'm already at 7,500 words, and I've got seven or eight more! But I'm sure you're all tired of watching. I'm such a chatterbox. And it's 22:16 at night, and for me, who slept last night, got up early this morning, didn't sleep at noon, and wasn't getting enough sleep for 14 hours straight, I should get some rest, so I decided to finish this article first, i'll tell the rest of the story later.
